sect1.para:
China is the second most populous country in Asia and the second most populous country in the world, with a population of 1.409 billion, dispersed over 3.7 million square miles of land (Wikipedia 
               2024
            ). Ninety-two percent of the population is Han; the remaining 8% is a mixture of 56 different nationalities, religions, and ethnic groups. Chinese people who live in the “Chinatowns” in the United States maintain many of their cultural beliefs and values and insist that health-care providers respect these values and beliefs with their interventions. In the United States, over two million people identify themselves as Chinese, with the largest communities residing in California, New York, Hawaii, and Texas. This aggregate profile of Chinese in the United States may not fit any one person due to individuality, acculturation, and other variant characteristics of culture (see Chap. 

                  1

            ).

listitem.para:
The official language of China is Mandarin (
                        pu tong hua
                     ), which is spoken by about 70% of the population. Other distinct dialects such as Cantonese, Fujianese, Shanghainese, Toishanese, and Hunanese are so different that often two groups cannot understand one another verbally. However, the written language is the same throughout the country, and consists of over 50,000 ideographs (about 5000 common ones).

Chinese culture, based on Confucianism, is known for its patriarchal traditions. Traditionally, women have often taken on the role of homemakers, overseeing all domestic responsibilities, while husbands have assumed the roles of family leaders and primary breadwinners (Zhong and Guo 
                        2018
                     ). In recent times, some men include housework, cooking, and cleaning as their responsibilities when their spouses work. Most believe that the family is most important and, thus, each family member assumes changes in roles to achieve this harmony.

In China, homosexuality has been legal since 1997. In 2019, same-sex marriage officially became legal in Taiwan (Executive Yuan 
                        2022
                     ), making it the first country in Asia and the 27th country in the world to recognize same-sex marriage. This granted equal marriage rights to both same-sex and heterosexual couples. However, the LGBT community still faces stigmatization in society, with gay relationships largely criticized at the national level and continuing to bear a stigma. Do not disclose same-sex relationships.

The ulna is longer than the radius. Hip measurements are significantly smaller than Westerners (Seidel et al. 
                        1994
                     ). Provide instruction on adequate calcium consumption to prevent osteoporosis and fractures. Ensure diet is low in lactose. Assess patients for genetic conditions before medications are prescribed.

Poor metabolism of mephenytoin occurs in 15–20% of Chinese. Sensitivity to beta blockers, such as propranolol, is evidenced by a decrease in overall blood levels accompanied by a more profound response. Atropine sensitivity is evidenced by an increased heart rate. Increased responses to antidepressants and neuroleptics occur at lower doses. Analgesics have been found to cause increased gastrointestinal side effects, despite a decreased sensitivity to them. Chinese people generally have an increased sensitivity to the effects of alcohol (Levy 
                        1993
                     ). Carefully monitor Chinese patients on medications such as propranolol, atropine, antidepressants, and neuroleptics.
